propOverview:
2945 Chapman Street is part of 2828 Ford Street. 
2945 Chapman Street is approximately 13,430 sq ft offered for lease in the historic Jingletown of Oakland. the entire property consists of 30,130 sq ft on approximately 1.15 acres of land. Currently Buildings 1 and 2 are fully occupied.
On the corner of 23td Avenue and 29th Avenue which is one block south from the entrance to Interstate 880 and one block North from the Park Street Bridge to Alameda.
Building 3 has access on Chapman Street with its own private entrance. There is a shared parking lot off Chapman street as well but parking will be limited within the shared parking lot. 
Jingletown is known as one of the fastest growing art communities in teh Bay Area with many live/work lofts and studio space surrounding the property.
Owner would like a non-profit business but is open to for profits. For-profits will be subject to paying their share of the pro-rata share of the property taxes for the building.
spaceBullets: Lease rate does not include utilities, property expenses or building services
spaceSummary: Hard to find industrial space in Oakland. Building size is 13,530 sq ft but can be divided and tenant does not need to take the upstairs space. Ceiling Height is approximately 14'6". Very secure space with metal doors and bars on skylights and windows. Most of the space is insulated. Large shared parking lot. Upstairs office space has a full kitchen and full bathroom.

highlights: +-7,600 SQ FT Industrial/Manufactuing Space,4,400 SQ FT Fully Built Out Office Space with Private Conference Room,18' Clear Height w/ 6" Slab Floor,3,200 SQ FT Insulated Warehouse,Heavy 3 Phase Power,Yard Space
propOverview:
+- 7,600 sq. ft. Industrial building for lease in the heart of Mountain Views’ South Moffett Triangle area.  This ½ of the building includes 3,200 sq. ft. of manufacturing/warehouse space with a bonus 2,200 sq. ft. mezzanine storage area and 4,400 feet of office space.  The Warehouse/Manufacturing space is insulated with an 18’ clear height with an oversized roll-up door sitting on a heavy duty 6” slab floor to accommodate your heavy duty use.  Power is 3 Phase and the manufacturing space is equipped with gas lines running down the sides of the walls to facilitate your specific lay-out needs.  The mezzanine area is accessible via forklift or stairs.  Adjacent the manufacturing space there is a separate lab room and a server room with dedicated circuits.   The 10 private offices are all good sized and anchored with 2 corner offices and a nice sized private conference room.  You will also find a breakroom/kitchenette along with 2 private baths and a separate shower facility with lockers.  Parking is +- 30 spaces which includes a off-street parking in the side and rear lots.  Street parking is also available.  The cul-de-sac location helps make this a semi-private area.  No cannabis.  
Easy access to Hwy’s 237 & 85 and just 1 mile to Mountain View’s Caltrain Station & Post Office and all the amenities that downtown Mountain View has to offer.

Only $37.87 psf and owner will carry. Includes 3632 W Clarendon (107-33-011A). Two buildings 13,200 sf on two 10,000 sf A-2 concrete paved and fenced lots. 3702 W Clarendon is  a 4,800 sf 2-story all free-span masonry all AC building. Second floor is a former sewing room and office with 3-restrooms that could be easily converted to a nice large watchman's apartment. First floor has a roll-up door and is currently used by a M-M tenant for automotive. 3632 W Clarendon is two connected building (3,600 & 4,484 sf). All AC former sewing facility with good power and a kiln. the building have newer foam roofs and have been re-painted. They present well. There is one active monitoring well on the property and several abandoned. Assumed to be ADEQ wells.
Clarendon is one street south of Indian School. Access Clarendon off 35th Ave or 43rd Ave. Direct access to Grand off 35th Ave and I-17 at Indian School Road & I-17.

highlights: Excellent Downtown Prescott Location,Fire Sprinklers Throughout,Industrial Transitions,50,000 SF Commercial Building,Amble on Site Parking - 200 Spaces,20 Feet Plus Clear Height
propOverview:
Industrial, Warehouse, Manufacturing & Commercial Office Space of approx. 67,120 SF, For Lease for $6.25 per sf modified gross. Also available For Sale at $3,350,000 or $49.91 per sf.  Current appraisal supporting the lease rate and sales price. Situated on 3.45 acres with 5 separate legal parcels, the property is Zoned Industrial Transition (IT).  Formerly the headquarters of Fortner Aerospace Manufacturing which moved in 2014, this facility is ideal for many other types of manufacturing operations. The property can also be repurpose and would be ideal for multiple school campus, church and/or religious institution uses, community organization uses or various indoor or outdoor recreations facilities. There are two primary buildings of 50,000 SF and 16,000 SF each. The larger 50,000 SF building offers approx. 15,000 SF of office space including: 20 private office, 2 conference rooms, employee transition room, 2 kitchenettes, 6 restrooms, 2 storage closets. Office space is located on both 1st and 2nd floors with elevator service avail for the northern most portion of the building. This building can be demised into multiple spaces and/or uses.
From Downtown Prescott head east on Sheldon St. to Pleasant St. Turn Left (North) on  Pleasant St. to property front entrance straight ahead.
Originally built in 1980 and several subsequent additions and renovations. Construction materials included a variety of block, steel frame and wood frame construction. Ample on-site parking with over 200 total spaces provided. The second building consist of approx. 16,000 SF and is single level offering 3 separate large open spaces totaling approx. 10,000 sf and additional office space totaling of approx. 5,000 sf.

propOverview:
Yorba Linda Business Park - Small Office Warehouse
Yorba Linda Business Park is an 115,760 SF multi-tenant industrial/flex property located in the Placentia East/Yorba Linda industrial submarket of Orange County, CA. The property consists of four (4) buildings situated on 9.13 acres with approximately 25-30% office finish, and was built in 1998 using concrete tilt up walls, structural steel, steel joists, and metal deck.
The property is well-located approximately 2 miles northeast of the 91 Freeway in Yorba Linda, and just west of the 241 Toll Road and east of the 55 Freeway. Yorba Linda is located in northeastern Orange County, boarded by Brea to the north, Anaheim to the south, unincorporated Orange County to the east and Placentia to the west.

propOverview:
148 Whitcomb is a 19,500 SF space consists of 13,000 SF of Industrial/Manufacturing and 6,500 SF of office. Located in the charming historic town of Colfax this building sits comfortably just off the I-80 freeway and is only 10 minutes from Auburn and 15 minutes from beautiful downtown Grass Valley. The building is shared with only one other tenant and sits on 3.62 acres in a lovely setting. This unit comes with its own private parking lot with 33 spaces. The other tenant, a printing company, has their own parking lot. (Office and Warehouse may be rented separately).
The large 13,000 SF warehouse is a large, open, airy room with high quality construction. There are two heavy-duty metal stairwells that lead up to the office space. A roll up door leads to the loading dock which is shared with the other tenant. Clearance in the warehouse is 26 feet and the ceiling reaches 35 feet at its highest peek. There are so many possibilities with this space. Combined with the 6,500 SF of office space this unit provides the right company the ability to produce their product from inspiration all the way to finished product in hand. You can house under one roof your design team, admin, manufacturing and storage. An exciting opportunity for a start-up or for an existing company who needs more space. While being outside of a major city this space provides a much more affordable option that is still well located and not too far from Sacramento and the Bay Area.
The office space features two large open concept areas which are surrounded by private office rooms. There are ten private office suites in total all with large widows and plenty of natural light. Nine of the ten office suites feature built-in closets. There is a kitchen with fridge, dishwasher and glass door that leads to a covered outdoor patio. There is a conference room with a wall of built-ins and wet sink. There is a media room with plenty of outlets for your copy machines, printers, etc. An IT room with structure already in place from previous tenants has AC, monitor and plenty of electrical. The office also has 2 ADA bathrooms, a walk-in mailroom closet and janitorial closet. A large storage area is located just off the main floor. The space is easy to move into and get going but of course an incoming tenant may customize the space to meet their specific needs. 
A great opportunity for the right company!

propOverview: The subject property is a 2-story industrial building located close to Fashion District & Arts District. In 2019 the property was completely refurbished like new. The subject building is a beautiful red brick building built originally in 1927 & 1937. The property features large and clean office area and warehouse area of 12' to 17' clear height. The property has a total of 800 amps of 3 phase electrical power, two 9'X10' freight elevators, 2 loading docks and 42 parking spaces on a detached lot. The property is divisible and great for any apparel manufacturing, internet sales office, studio, production and creative office/warehouse uses. Omega Cinema Props, Inc. will relocate to the 245,000 SF building across the street at 1515 E. 15th Street by the end of 2019. This company provides props for television and film productions and had been in its Hollywood location for more than 90 years.

propOverview: This building located off Airport Road in Redding, CA, Shasta County. It sits in the back of a high end complex and is the largest building in the complex. It is a newer building with good security fencing that allows for a large yard space on the West and North sides. It has nice office space in the front of the building, allowing tenant to partition heat and air as needed. Behind the offices are 2 22' industrial/warehouse spaces separated by a full height wall running the entire length of the building. Being situated in Shasta county, outside Redding city limits, provides use advantages. Inside building, there are also 4 large mezzanine spaces great for storage. Curb appeal is outstanding with large windows with awnings to let in natural light into all the office spaces. The property is part of a probate estate and court confirmation is required.

spaceSummary: A 15,400 square foot industrial building is located in the Skypark Industrial Park.  The building consists of a steel-frame building with concrete perimeter slab foundation and sheet metal exterior.  There is a fenced in secured yard in the rear of the building.  The office area of the building is located on the eastern elevation and is wood-frame construction with Hardiplank exterior siding, and a composition shingle roof.  The interior of the building is comprised of nearly half of flex conditioned warehouse and office. The office portion is serviced by packaged forced-air units. hoodMarket: The Airport Area is one of the densest neighborhoods in the Inland Empire in terms of population and business presence. Abundant in infrastructure, the neighborhood is served by multiple freeways and rail lines that provide access to the twin ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach. Ontario International Airport transports over 780,000 tons of cargo per year, in addition to more than 5 million passengers.,Some of the nation’s largest companies have well-established distribution centers in the Airport Area, including Amazon, Walmart, Target, Georgia-Pacific, Kimberly-Clark, and Bridgestone. Some of the largest logistics companies in the nation are also here, including UPS, DHL, and GEODIS. Manufacturing has a rich history in the Airport Area, specifically among companies that produce steel products and related items. The former Kaiser Steel Plant in Fontana, a 4-million-square-foot facility, has been owned and operated by California Steel Products since 1984.,The Airport Area has had more than its fair share of industrial development over the past 10 years, and demand has equally matched supply. Aside from containing more loading docks, higher clear heights, and additional windows, modern industrial buildings tend to contain sizeable office space suitable for professional and administrative workers. Businesses can benefit from proximity to a growing pool of labor in the Airport Area, as high levels of construction of both single-family and multifamily housing has outpaced the broader Inland Empire market.

hoodMarket: Santa Ana is supported by arterial freeways (I-5, I-405, SR 22, SR 55), which provide it with easy access across all of Orange County. Additionally, John Wayne Airport is a stone’s throw away from the submarket’s southern border, and the submarket is served by the Union Pacific Railroad. The Airport Area location is filled with restaurants, retailers, and office campuses and connects local logistics supply to the ports in Los Angeles and Long Beach. ,As one of the few areas in Orange County to have available space that can accommodate users of a significant size, Santa Ana is home to several notable tenants. Outside of large logistics firms such as Amazon and Pioneer Packing, aerospace firms including Cherry Aerospace, Airborne Systems, and GE Aviation maintain significant footprints in Santa Ana.,Although the industrial vacancy rate is elevated above the low Orange County rate, demand remains firmly in place for the area’s warehouse, distribution, and manufacturing facilities interested in tapping into transportation corridors and population nodes. Rent levels offer an affordable alternative to tenants seeking space and easy access to the southern parts of Orange County.

hoodMarket: Sylmar is the northernmost neighborhood in the sprawling City of Los Angeles. Its distance from the area’s premiere employment and residential hubs give the area a suburban feel, but interstates 5, 405, and 210, collectively some of Los Angeles’ most heavily traveled highways, converge here. Interstate 5 is California’s main north-south artery and continues on into the Central Valley, while Interstate 210 offers direct access to the Inland Empire’s vast industrial landscape.,Manufacturing has been a staple of the area since the 1970s, with companies like L-3 Ocean Systems, Abbot/St. Jude Medical, and PPG Aerospace maintaining significant manufacturing operations here. While overall manufacturing employment has been declining in Los Angeles for decades, the growth of the logistics sector has helped offset those losses. ,The area’s strategic location at the conjunction of several major highways helps underpin strong demand for industrial space. New industrial development is minimal though, a common refrain across Los Angeles County.
propOverview: Located in Los Angeles’s northernmost neighborhood, 15148 Bledsoe Street in Sylmar, California, provides an excellent corporate image and location. Initially constructed in 1969, the entire building was renovated in 2015, and Unit B features office space with modern finishes and all the industrial amenities necessary for today’s industrial businesses. The 3,767 square-foot office overlooks the warehouse area and features offices and a conference room with attractive floor-to-ceiling glass partitions. The warehouse area features clear heights ranging from 14’-18’, 4 (four) covered truck well loading positions and 3 (three) ground level doors, and 1000-amps of 480-volt, 3-phase, 4-wire power throughout. The property provides multiple, convenient distribution options with only a 5-minute drive to the 5 and 210 freeways and a 10-minute drive to the 118, 405, and 14 freeways. The Bob Hope Airport can be reached in an 18-minute drive and the Los Angeles International Airport is just 35 minutes away, the Port of Long Beach is only 40 miles away, and the UP- Los Angeles rail line is only 21.6 miles from the property. For employees, the Sylmar/San Fernando Commuter Rail (Antelope Valley Line) is a 6-minute drive away, and the property is surrounded by densely packed residential neighborhoods. For shopping, dining, and conveniences, the Sylmar Towne Shopping Center is 6 minutes away and is surrounded by the bustling commercial district at the intersection of Hubbard Street and Glenoaks Boulevard.

hoodMarket: Camarillo is a coastal community steeped in history as an agricultural center with a diverse population. Today, the area is one of the largest industrial regions in Ventura County, in spite of legislative initiatives aimed at conserving open space and agricultural land. ,The largest industrial buildings are multi-tenant buildings with roughly 400,000 square feet, limiting opportunities to lease large spaces over 100,000 square feet. Camarillo has the only outlet shopping center in Ventura County, an attractive amenity for local employees and for the legions of visitors travelling between Los Angeles and Santa Barbara.,Among the diverse industrial make-up of firms located in Camarillo are many advanced manufacturing companies producing electronics, machinery, aerospace, and transportation goods. Although the area has easy access to the twin ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach, as well as the Port of Hueneme, few third-party logistics firms are based here. ,Rent growth has been above-average over the past five years. New development has been primarily of 10,000- to 60,000-square-foot facilities, with a few outliers. Available land is limited, and neighborhood opposition to further industrial development will keep existing properties as attractive options.

hoodMarket: Paramount is a small city in southern Los Angeles County, just north of Long Beach. Interstate 710, the main highway link to the massive twin ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach, forms the western edge of the city, and Interstate 105 runs east-west through the northern portion. This is a dense, built-out section of Los Angeles, with an industrial hub nestled between several residential neighborhoods. ,The local economy is primarily comprised of small businesses, although a few major industrial operations dot the landscape. Ralphs owns a 550,000-square-foot distribution center in the center of town, and aerospace manufacturers Carlton Forge Works and Castle Metals Aerospace have their primary facilities here as well. ,As in much of Los Angeles, the heavily built-out character of the area prevents any significant new industrial development. Vacancies remain low as a result, although industrial space here is available for a slight discount compared to the greater Los Angeles average.
propOverview: Located adjacent to an established industrial sector in Paramount, 7110 Rosecrans Avenue provides amenities typically reserved for office users, all while enjoying easy accessibility to the area’s major highways. Recent major renovations include both interior and exterior upgrades. Brand new, two-story office space offers a spacious conference room, open, customizable workspace, and partitioned areas that overlook the loading docks. Loading options include two drive-in doors, one at the front of the warehouse and one at the back, and two interior, dock-high positions that offer a covered truck well. The building also features a 24’ clear height, 100 amps of 120/208-volt, 3-phase, 4-wire power with options to expand up to 1,000 amps, new LED lighting, new ESFR sprinklers, and a shared 6,000 square-foot covered storage/yard area that is completely fenced. Commutability and distribution options include just a 5-minute drive to both the 105 and 710 freeways and a 10-minute drive to the 605 and 91 freeways. The Long Beach-Daugherty Field Airport can be reached in 14 minutes, the Los Angeles International Airport in 22, and the Titan Terminal and Transport, Inc. rail line in just 11, providing further conveniences for a variety of industrial uses. For dining and entertainment, employees enjoy multiple options in less than a mile walk, including El Compa Restaurant, Tortas Chingonas, Taqueria 2 Amigos, and the Paramount Entertainment Center, featuring the daily Paramount Swap Meet and the Paramount Drive-In Theatres. This prime Paramount location offers access to 16-million citizens within 50 miles.

propOverview: Located in the heart of the San Francisco Bay Area, 4225 Hacienda Drive is the Tri-Valley’s premier warehouse, distribution, and regional headquarters facility. This multi-tenanted building is comprised of 389,673 square feet on a 22.38-acre parcel in the Hacienda Business Park. The building features a new roof, 28’-30’ interior clear heights, 41 dock-high doors that measure 8’x10’, and two grade-level doors, making it an ideal property for logistics-focused companies. Additionally, the building offers 2,800-amp, 277/480-volt, 3-phase power, forklift charging stations, and an in-place exhaust system. 4225 Hacienda Drive is well-positioned for any business serving local customers and on the West Coast. Three freeway intersections directly serve the Hacienda Business Park: two off I-580, and one off nearby I-680, giving the site the best freeway access of any business center in the Bay Area. The property is located just 20 miles from the California Central Valley, 30 minutes from the Port of Oakland, 51 minutes from the Port of Redwood City, 26 minutes from the Quality Transport, Inc. rail line in Fremont, and within 30 miles of both the Oakland and the San Jose International Airports. The location also offers many commute benefits because of its reverse-commute location and proximity to the Bay Area Rapid Transit (BART) system, with trains arriving every 15 minutes during peak travel hours. Many companies have already located their businesses in this desirable area, and corporate neighbors for 4225 Hacienda Drive include Boeing, Integen, Bio-Rad, and Roche.

hoodMarket: The Airport Area is one of the densest neighborhoods in the Inland Empire in terms of population and business presence. Abundant in infrastructure, the neighborhood is served by multiple freeways and rail lines that provide access to the twin ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach. Ontario International Airport transports over 780,000 tons of cargo per year, in addition to more than 5 million passengers.,Some of the nation’s largest companies have well-established distribution centers in the Airport Area, including Amazon, Walmart, Target, Georgia-Pacific, Kimberly-Clark, and Bridgestone. Some of the largest logistics companies in the nation are also here, including UPS, DHL, and GEODIS. Manufacturing has a rich history in the Airport Area, specifically among companies that produce steel products and related items. The former Kaiser Steel Plant in Fontana, a 4-million-square-foot facility, has been owned and operated by California Steel Products since 1984.,The Airport Area has had more than its fair share of industrial development over the past 10 years, and demand has equally matched supply. Aside from containing more loading docks, higher clear heights, and additional windows, modern industrial buildings tend to contain sizeable office space suitable for professional and administrative workers. Businesses can benefit from proximity to a growing pool of labor in the Airport Area, as high levels of construction of both single-family and multifamily housing has outpaced the broader Inland Empire market.

A true commuter’s dream, the rental space offers super convenient access to three major roadways: I-10, I-15, and Highway 60. Our unique common area is a living-room-style space designed for creativity, comfort, and productivity.

hoodMarket: Supported by its central location and bracketed by several arterial freeways, Sorrento Mesa’s profile has taken off in recent years. The neighborhood provides plentiful housing and is within close proximity to high-end shopping, restaurants, and San Diego’s crystalline beaches. Sorrento Mesa’s employers recruit from the pipeline of students graduating from neighboring UC San Diego. High household incomes and advanced education levels are common among residents here.,While Sorrento Mesa was dependent on Qualcomm, its lineup of industrial tenants has diversified significantly over the past several years. Along with UTC and Torrey Pines, Sorrento Mesa has become one of San Diego’s core innovation hubs and includes notable tenants such as Qualcomm, Thermo Fisher Scientific, Meggitt Polymers, CV Sciences, and Quidel Corporation, among others. Green Flash, one of San Diego’s most prominent brewers, also calls Sorrento Mesa home.,Although the vacancy rate is susceptible to significant swings due to large industrial tenants, demand remains firmly locked in place for one of San Diego’s most desirable neighborhoods for industrial tenants. And while rent levels are among the highest in San Diego, they still offer a discount compared with more coastal industrial areas such as Torrey Pines or UTC.
propOverview: 10015 Waples Court is located in Sorrento Valley which was originally designed as San Diego's industrial district and paved the way for several well-known corporations and industries to headquarter there, such as Qualcomm, Dexcom, Arena Pharmaceuticals, and Accelrys US. Due to the short 15-minute drive to the University of California in San Diego, Sorrento Valley organically strayed from the original growth plan and has since become a desirable destination for residents, which provides businesses with a strong industrial infrastructure and a built-in labor force. Recognized as one of the leading high-tech hubs in the US, San Diego’s innovation economy is anchored by established companies such as Intel, Sony, and Hewlett Packard. San Diego is home to the largest concentration of military in the world, the largest federal military workforce in the nation, and some of the world’s largest research and development companies. Given the highly-skilled workforce, robust training programs, and proximity to Mexico, San Diego is also a hub for advanced manufacturing companies. In addition, the 1,100 life sciences companies and more than 80 research institutes are major drivers of the innovative local economy. 10015 Waples Court is located a half-mile off Mira Mesa Boulevard, the main thoroughfare through the industrial parks of Sorrento Valley, and provides easy access to major transportation routes with a 5-minute drive to I-805 and 10 minutes to I-5. The Port of San Diego is a 30-minute drive and oversees two major cargo terminals, the 96-acre Tenth Avenue Marine Terminal and the 135-acre National City Marine Terminal. 10015 Waples Court is under new ownership with modernizing renovations underway featuring 9,200 square feet of new, highly upgraded office space, 12 large grade-level doors, 9 dock positions, ESFR sprinkler system, and skylights. The facility boasts 31'-33' clear heights and 1,200 amps of 277/480 volt power with a 3-phase/4-wire system.

hoodMarket: Santa Clarita is situated at the northern extreme of the Los Angeles metro area. Mountainous geography separates the region from the L.A. basin’s notorious suburban sprawl, giving it a somewhat secluded feel, and Downtown Los Angeles is an hour’s drive away on a good day. The region straddles I-5, California’s main north-south artery, giving it a desirable location for logistics operations moving goods from the ports of Long Beach and Los Angeles up the West Coast to Northern California and the Pacific Northwest.,Most industrial activity is concentrated north of the Santa Clarita River in close proximity to I-5. Third-party logistics companies comprise a major portion of the tenant base, with a mix of light manufacturing operations and support services for L.A.’s massive entertainment industry.,In comparison to the rest of L.A.’s drum-tight industrial market, tenants here may find a few more availabilities. This is one of the last corners of the region with significant amounts of raw, developable land, and speculative construction is more prevalent here than almost anywhere else in the county.,Santa Clarita’s distance from the ports and heart of the metro limits the appeal for regional last-mile distribution operations. Industrial rents tend to be more affordable than in more centrally located industrial hubs. However, the area’s strategic position as the last sizable community along I-5 before departing L.A County to points north helps to underpin demand and continues to draw the attention of developers and investors.
propOverview: 29003 Avenue Sherman is a state-of-the-art industrial facility located within the prestigious Valencia Commerce Center. The impressive building was recently renovated, featuring sleek designs and premium finishes, creating a headquarters atmosphere and adding a plethora of on-site amenities. The immaculate 11,799-square-foot office features a two-story reception area complete with stone tile floors and a furnished waiting area, a staff lounge with a kitchen and exercise room on the first floor, and a break room with a coffee bar on the second floor. There are three large bullpens, a conference room, private restrooms with showers, a lunch patio, and nine private offices, four of which are on the second floor overlooking the warehouse. The expansive 56,324-square-foot warehouse boasts 26' to 28' clear heights and 2,000 amps of 480-volt, 3-phase, 4-wire power. Exceptional loading is provided with two 12' by 14' ground-level doors and four 9' by 14' dock-high doors, with the ability to add a fifth dock to rapidly accommodate any arising need. 29003 Avenue Sherman is five minutes from the Interstate 5/Highway 126 interchange and within 20 minutes of eight major highways and freeways. Highway 126 offers drives to the Port of Hueneme in an hour and 10 minutes, and Interstate 5, the main north/south freeway running along the west coast, opens up access to the region and reaches the ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach in an hour and 45 minutes. Other nearby transportation channels include the Bob Hope Airport, a 35-minute drive, and the Union Pacific Railroad in Los Angeles, a 50-minute drive. 29003 Avenue Sherman places businesses at the core of a well-educated workforce and a thriving community, known as the best-kept secret in Southern California. This building is also available for sale at $149 per square foot.

propOverview:
Ideally situated at the center of Los Angeles County and along the bustling Alameda Corridor, this Hub City warehouse is perfect for teams in many of Southern California’s fast-growing industries. Divide or merge your space into private or shared offices, common areas and conference rooms, or corporate suites. With front-desk service, business-class printing, mail and package handling, A/V equipment, and high-speed internet, your team will have everything it needs to succeed. Enjoy amenities such as bike storage and kitchens stocked with fresh micro-brewed coffee and fruit-infused water. When a business lunch is in order, an array of Asian fusion, Mexican, and soul food restaurants are minutes away. A range of 100–30,000 square feet is available in the industrial part of the building, with 100–2,000 square feet for rent in the office area. Pricing is competitive and lease terms are negotiable.  All warehouse spaces can be built-to-suit your needs and we have experienced professionals who will work with you to ensure that your space matches your business needs. We have at each Cubework location on-site staff from front desk-service to personal support for you throughout the workweek. Our cleaning crew helps around the clock keeping common areas, meeting rooms, and private offices looking their spiffiest. 
Cubework is the fastest growing industrial work space in the US adding a new location every 10 days!  The company has over 30 locations with 4 million square feet of modern industrial coworking space in 25 cities.  For an inviting warehouse and office coworking experience that puts you in the center of the action, schedule a visit today!

propOverview:
Former Whirlpool manufacturing and distribution campus.
Fort Smith is the second-largest city in Arkansas.  With a large metro area population it is a regional manufacturing center, with major plants located in the city operated by Rheem, Trane, Georgia-Pacific, Gerber, Kraft Planters Peanuts, Mitsubishi Power Systems Americas, Mars Petcare, Umarex USA, Graphic Packaging, and many others.
Fort Smith is home to several corporations including Baldor Electric Company, a member of the ABB Group, Arkansas Best Corporation, and poultry company OK Industries.
Fort Smith is a major transportation hub for the surrounding region.  It sits at the crossroads of two major interstate highways, is surrounded on three sides by the Arkansas River, is served by one major and two regional/switching railroad companies, and is the home of a regional airport.

propOverview:
VERY RARE! 4 of the 5 units could be considered the nicest climate controlled, bathroom/office included storage units in town. This unicorn of a property is one of the largest and cleanest industrial/warehouse complexes in Lake Havasu City.  
1. Unit 100 - The largest unit splits are 11,050 Sqft of warehouse and 3439 Sqft of office. The property has ample parking, plenty of room for semis to maneuver into any of the four loading docks, and has an additional 14' roll up door. The warehouse house has 16-20' high ceilings for plenty of rack storage as well. Also, if you're looking for more space, there is a total 5 units available totaling 25,867 sqft.
2. Unit 120 - Drive through 14' Roll up doors. The unit is 43.33' wide x 113.67' long with high ceilings. Big open space with endless possibilities. 
3. Unit 122 - 14' Roll up door. The unit is 24.33' wide x 74.34' long with high ceilings and 60' pull out and in driveway. 
4. Unit 124 - 14' Roll up door. The unit is 25' wide x 74.34' long with high ceilings and 60' pull out and in driveway.
5. Unit 128 - 14' Roll up door. The unit is 37.50' wide x 74.34' long with high ceilings and 60' pull out and in driveway
Side note - Units 120, 122, and 124 could be combined into a single unit.

propOverview:
Union Pacific Railroad' s intermodal network reaches more markets, more frequently than any other North American railroad. With 32,000 miles of track, their vast network provides extensive access to intermodal ramps in rowing population centers across the Western United States. Connecting railroads further extend the market reach, to the East and Canada, as well as Mexico, where Union Pacific offers unmatched intermodal coverage and serves all six major Mexico gateways. In addition, Union Pacific Railroad provides service offerings for dry and refrigerated Container on Flat Car (COFC), and Trailer on Flat Car (TOFC) equipment and they are the only Western railroad to offer their customers access to North America' s largest fleet of rail-owned domestic containers. With unbeatable domestic and international transportation solutions, innovative customer tools and commitment to capacity growth, Union Pacific is the premier intermodal solution in North America.
Being located within a Foreign Trade Zone, the Port of Tucson provides a location for inbound shipping, receiving and warehousing.Being located within a Foreign Trade Zone, the Port of Tucson provides a location for inbound shipping, receiving and warehousing.

propOverview:
28,912sf office/warehouse (26,499sf warehouse, 1,232sf office) located at 250 Jacintoport Blvd. in the Mobile River Industrial Park in Saraland, Alabama.  The warehouse is climate controlled and features 7 dock height doors and 24' eave height.  Column spacing is 30' x 73'.  Constructed in 1998 and zoned for light industrial users.  39,600sf of the building is occupied by Cambria Company, a quartz countertop manufacturer and retailer.  National Tire Wholesale occupies 64,000sf.  The 28,912sf vacancy is situated between teh tewo tenants.  The property offers convenient access to I-65 via Hwy. 43 and Hwy 158.  Being north of I-10 affords truck drivers the opportunity to avoid the tunnels that frequently congest I-10 in downtown Mobile.  Eastbound drivers can cross the Mobile River via the Cochran Bridge north of downtown and connect with I-10 on the east side of the tunnels.  West bound drivers can access I-10 where I-65 terminates, again avoiding traffic cause by the tunnels.
The building is located in the Mobile River Industrial Park in Saraland, AL, along with several other light industrial operations.  The eastern border of the park is state owned wilderness and there the local police station is located near the entrance of the park on its west side.  As a result, there is a high level of security at the property.   
Saraland is a suburb of Mobile in the northern part of Mobile County.  The property is located in the Mobile River Industrial Park, which is located along a vibrant retail corridor.  The eastern border of the park is state owned wilderness and the Saraland police station is located near the entrance of the park on its west side, affording tenants in the park a highly secure environment.  Saraland is a rapidly growing community due in large part to its independent, autonomous public school system.  New residential subdivisions are under construction and a Mobile-based hospital system if building a new campus at one of Saraland's two interstate interchanges.  Major retailers continue to open stores in Saraland.

highlights: (1) dock height door,Skylights,Insulated walls,(6) short doors (2.5' high),Wet sprinkler system,Convenient access to Hwy. 43, I-65, I-10
propOverview:
9,600sf of office/warehouse featuring (1) dock height door, (6) short doors (2.5' high), (2) restrooms, break room, insulated walls and wet sprinkler system.  The warehouse is heated, but not cooled.  Previously occupied by an auto parts distributor.
The property offers convenient access to I-65 via Hwy. 43  and Hwy. 158.  Being north of I-10 affords truck drivers the opportunity to avoid the tunnels that frequently congest I-10 in downtown Mobile.  Eastbound drivers can cross the Mobile River via the Cochrane Bridge north of downtown and connect with I-10 on the east side of the tunnels.  West bound drivers can access I-10 where I-65 terminates, again avoiding traffic caused by the tunnels.
The building is located in the Mobile River Industrial Park in Saraland, Alabama, along with several other light industrial operations.  The eastern border of the park is a state owned wilderness area and a Saraland police precinct is located at the entrance to the park on its west side, affording tenants a secure work environment.   The Mobile River Industrial Park is located on Highway 43, a vibrant retail corridor in Saraland.
Saraland is a suburb of Mobile in the northern part of Mobile County.  Saraland is a rapidly growing community due in large part to its independent, autonomous public school system.  New residential subdivisions are under construction and a Mobile-based hospital system is building a new campus at one of Saraland's two interstate interchanges.  Major retailers continue to open stores in Saraland.
